Article currently states following to be ISRO's motto, it was part of banner image but didn't feature on 'About Us' page before website update around December 2014.{{cite web |title=ISRO  'About Us' |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141027123733/http://www.isro.org:80/scripts/Aboutus.aspx}}

{{Quote|text=Space technology in the Service of humankind.}}

After the website update though, we have seen a change in ISRO's vision statement and old 'motto' is replaced by following.{{cite web |title=ISRO 'About Us' |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203045241/https://www.isro.gov.in/about-isro/vision-and-mission-statements |accessdate=3 December 2018}}

{{Quote|text=Harness space technology for national development, while pursuing space science research and planetary exploration.}}

This is very significant shift and appears to have so far gone unnoticed. I suggest we replace the 'Motto' with a Vision Statement if these can be considered official statements of much significance.

